spanishExample: A la reina le gustan los jóvenes.
englishTranslation: The queen likes young people.

spanishExample: A nuestra maestra le importaba nuestra familia.
englishTranslation: Our teacher (f) cared about our family.

spanishExample: A nuestra profesora siempre le gustaban estos.
englishTranslation: Our professor(f) always liked these.

spanishExample: A tu jefa no le ha gustado tu trabajo por un tiempo.
englishTranslation: Your boss(f) hasn’t liked your work for a while.

spanishExample: Al policía le gustaba preocuparse por algo que no importaba.
englishTranslation: The police officer liked to get worried about something that didn’t matter.

spanishExample: El rey dijo que esto es importante.
englishTranslation: The king said this is important.

spanishExample: Espero que te guste esta comida, él es un maestro de esto.
englishTranslation: I hope you like this food, he is a master at this.

spanishExample: La policía tuvo que hablar con su jefe.
englishTranslation: The police officer(f) had to talk to her boss(m).

spanishExample: La presidenta es una maestra de estas cosas.
englishTranslation: The president(f) is a master at these things.

spanishExample: Le importará a la doctora si el rey está mal.
englishTranslation: It will matter to the doctor(f) if the king is unwell.

spanishExample: Le importaría al agente si estuvieran juntos.
englishTranslation: It would be important for the agent if you(plural) were together.

spanishExample: Le preocupa el perro porque está un poco loco.
englishTranslation: She worries about the dog because it’s a bit crazy.

spanishExample: Le tiene que importar al maestro o es un mal maestro.
englishTranslation: It has to matter to the teacher or he is a bad teacher.

spanishExample: Lo más importante es que el agente hable con nosotros.
englishTranslation: The most important (thing) is that the agent talks with us.

spanishExample: Lo más importante es que ellos no se preocupen.
englishTranslation: The most important (thing) is that they don’t get worried.

spanishExample: Me preocupo por ti porque me gustas.
englishTranslation: I worry about you because I like you.

spanishExample: Mis oportunidades les importan a mis padres y a mis profesores.
englishTranslation: My opportunities are important to my parents and to my professors.

spanishExample: No creo que le importe porque le gusto.
englishTranslation: I don’t think she cares because she likes me.

spanishExample: No se preocupe, señor presidente, la reina estará aquí pronto.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Don’t worry, Mr. President, the queen will be here soon.

spanishExample: No te preocupes, creo que te va a gustar.
englishTranslation: Don’t worry, I think you’re going to like it.

spanishExample: No tienes que preocuparte, pero deberías ir al doctor.
englishTranslation: You don’t have to worry, but you should go to the doctor.

spanishExample: Te preocupas mucho.
englishTranslation: You worry too much.
